  "prompt": "How do I know if someone blocks me on Facebook messenger?",
  "response": "If someone blocks you on Facebook Messenger, there are several signs that can indicate this:\n\n1. **Message Delivery Status**: When you send a message, it may show only one checkmark (indicating that it has been sent) and never progress to a double checkmark (indicating that it has been delivered). This means the message is not reaching the recipient.\n\n2. **Searching for Profile**: If you try to search for their profile using the search bar and you cannot find it, or if you once could see their profile and now it appears to be invisible, you might be blocked.\n\n3. **Previous Conversations**: Previous conversations with the person may appear differently. The chat might show \"This person is unavailable on Messenger\" or the user's profile picture might be missing.\n\n4. **Call Attempt**: Any calls attempted to the person on Messenger may fail. The call might not go through, and you may get an error message.\n\n5. **No Interaction**: If you can see their profile or previous messages but cannot interact (like sending messages or calls) with them, this could be a sign of being blocked.\n\nNote that these signs are similar when someone deactivates their account, changes their privacy settings, or if there is a connectivity issue. Only the person who blocked you knows the exact reason for these changes in interaction possibilities.",
